ually%20bold%20strategy%20of%20writing%20%2430%20million%20checks%20to%20seed-stage%20companies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EZhan%20believes%20VC%20is%20undergoing%20a%20transformation%20that%20requires%20firms%20to%20pounce%20with%20big%20checks%20very%20early.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20just%2029%2C%20Brian%20Zhan%2C%20who%20practices%20what%20he%20describes%20as%20%26quot%3Bnerdy%20investing%2C%26quot%3B%20has%20already%20made%20early%20bets%20on%20buzzy%20AI%20companies%20now%20valued%20in%20the%20billions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20quietly%20leaving%20Silicon%20Valley%20VC%20firm%20CRV%20this%20summer%2C%20Zhan%20recently%20joined%20Striker%20Venture%20Partners%2C%20where%20he%20and%20veteran%20investor%20Max%20Gazor%20plan%20to%20upend%20traditional%20VC%20playbooks%20with%20a%20%24165%20million%20fund%20that%20aims%20to%20make%20massive%20seed%20bets%20on%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20AI%20startups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20only%20investing%20in%2010%20companies%20per%20fund%2C%20and%20we're%20going%20to%20show%20up%20with%20checks%20up%20to%20%2430%20million%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhan%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20takes%20conviction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%2430%20million%20is%20what%20companies%20typically%20raise%20in%20a%20later%20funding%20round%20once%20they%20have%20achieved%20product-market%20fit%2C%20but%20Zhan%20believes%20VC%20is%20undergoing%20a%20radical%20transformation%20that%20requires%20firms%20to%20pounce%20with%20big%20checks%20when%20an%20early%20kernel%20of%20an%20idea%20presents%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSeed-stage%20investing%20is%20moving%20earlier%20and%20earlier%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSeed%20rounds%20today%20are%20often%20just%2022-year-old%20founders%20with%20a%20great%20idea.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhan%2C%20who%20studied%20computer%20science%20at%20Northwestern%20University%20and%20started%20his%20career%20writing%20code%20at%20Facebook%2C%20is%20emblematic%20of%20a%20shift%20taking%20place%20in%20venture%2C%20where%20investors%20switch%20firms%20more%20often%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftechnical-has-become-paramount-for-young-talent-at-vc-firms-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etechnical%20backgrounds%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20prized%20above%20MBAs%20because%20many%20of%20the%20most%20promising%20new%20startups%20have%20few%20business%20metrics%20to%20evaluate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20on%20the%20Facebook%20data%20team%20where%20I%20saw%20a%20pattern%20that%20really%20stuck%20with%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20best%20technical%20minds%20at%20the%20company%20were%20founding%20startups%20and%20then%20struggling%20to%20raise%20meaningful%20capital%2C%20despite%20having%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20that%20Silicon%20Valley%20normally%20drools%20over.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20started%20angel%20investing%20in%20his%20spare%20time%2C%20writing%20small%20checks%20into%20projects%20led%20by%20former%20Facebook%20engineers.%20At%20CRV%2C%20Zhan%20transitioned%20to%20a%20full-time%20VC%20role%2C%20making%20early%20bets%20on%20Skild%20AI%2C%20Dyna%20Robotics%2C%20and%20Periodic%20Labs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%2C%20these%20companies%20are%20some%20of%20the%20best-known%20companies%20in%20AI%2C%20but%20back%20at%20the%20seed%20round%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20VCs%20just%20didn't%20really%20know%20who%20these%20founders%20were%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20biggest%20win%20so%20far%20is%20the%20model%20startup%20Reflection%20AI%2C%20which%20he%20views%20as%20proof%20that%20VCs%20should%20not%20be%20afraid%20to%20pay%20up%20in%20seed%20rounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhan%20co-led%20Reflection%20AI's%20seed%20round%20just%20last%20year%20at%20a%20%24200%20million%20valuation%2C%20a%20very%20expensive%20price%20that%20many%20other%20VCs%20passed%20up.%20Last%20month%2C%20the%20company%20raised%20%242%20billion%20at%20a%20valuation%20of%20%248%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFounders%20want%20someone%20who%20can%20speak%20their%20language%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Misha%20Laskin%2C%20CEO%20and%20cofounder%20of%20Reflection%20AI.%20%26quot%3BBrian%20is%20rare%20in%20that%20he's%20actually%20done%20the%20work%2C%20is%20incredibly%20well%20connected%2C%20and%20is%20insightful%20about%20what's%20happening%20at%20the%20frontier.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b3233bfa-7f8f-4b2d-bbd4-4bc4d8a1d36f%5C%22%3EExcited%20about%20AI%20for%20science%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EZhan%20grew%20up%20in%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20Beijing%2C%20and%20Palo%20Alto.%20His%20older%20sister%20is%20Stephanie%20Zhan%2C%20a%20general%20partner%20at%20Sequoia%20Capital%2C%20who%20was%20also%20an%20early%20backer%20of%20Reflection%20AI%20and%20Skild%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20say%20we%20have%20very%20similar%20tastes%2C%20and%20sometimes%20we%20land%20on%20the%20same%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20Brian%20Zhan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsked%20if%20they%20will%20be%20discussing%20deals%20around%20the%20Thanksgiving%20table%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20we%20keep%20work%20separate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20VCs%20spend%20their%20days%20in%20coffee%20shops%20meeting%20as%20many%20founders%20as%20possible%2C%20Zhan%20finds%20it%20more%20useful%20to%20devote%20hours%20a%20day%20to%20reading%20the%20latest%20AI%20research%20curated%20by%20his%20own%20custom%20AI%20assistant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20he%20was%20drawn%20to%20reunite%20with%20Gazor%2C%20an%20MIT%20Ph.D.%20dropout%20who%20has%20appeared%20four%20times%20on%20the%20Forbes%20Midas%20list%2C%20because%20of%20their%20similar%20intellectual%20style.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20spend%20all%20morning%20reading%20papers%20and%20trying%20to%20identify%20the%20trends%20and%20who%20has%20the%20most%20exciting%20ideas%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhan%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20take%20very%20few%20meetings%20every%20day.%20We%20just%20spend%20more%20time%20figuring%20out%20what%20the%20frontier%20is%2C%20and%20when%20we%20reach%20out%20to%20founders%2C%20we%20have%20already%20made%20up%20our%20mind%20to%20go%20back%20to%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGazor%2C%20who%20is%20probably%20best%20known%20for%20his%20early%20investment%20in%20Airtable%2C%20helped%20recruit%20Zhan%20to%20CRV%20in%202023%20and%20wanted%20to%20work%20with%20him%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20saw%20him%20become%20one%20of%20the%20most%20trusted%20advisors%20to%20some%20of%20the%20most%20high-profile%20AI%20founders%2C%20and%20I%20was%20really%20in%20awe%20of%20how%20he%20related%20to%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Gazor%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe's%20got%20a%20fantastic%20trajectory%20ahead%20of%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhan%20says%20he%20is%20most%20excited%20about%20founders%20who%20are%20harnessing%20the%20power%20of%20AI%20for%20science%2C%20such%20as%20William%20Fedus%2C%20a%20former%20OpenAI%20researcher%20who%20recently%20cofounded%20Periodic%20Labs%20to%20automate%20scientific%20discovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BImagine%20if%20we%20could%20use%20AI%20to%20dramatically%20shorten%20drug%20discovery%20timelines%3F%26quot%3B%20Zhan%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20AI%20for%20science%20will%20become%20as%20big%20a%20category%20as%20AI%20for%20robotics%20is%20today.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvc-deploying-a-bold-strategy-for-investing-in-ai-startups-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1763978402000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69209a9fabd5e944effb3fc7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvc-deploying-a-bold-strategy-for-investing-in-ai-startups-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Brian%20Zhan%20and%20Max%20Gazor%2C%20formerly%20of%20CRV%2C%20will%20employ%20an%20unusually%20bold%20high-risk%2Fhigh-reward%20strategy%2C%20making%20massive%20bets%20out%20of%20their%20debut%20fund.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%2