sider.com%2F6920ab32e1a9cbb014debc48%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202024%2C%20Magdalena%20Robinson%20was%20laid%20off%20from%20her%20job%20as%20a%20vice%20president%20of%20talent%20acquisition%20at%20a%20media%20agency.%20The%20news%20came%20as%20a%20shock%20%E2%80%94%20by%20all%20accounts%20she%20was%20doing%20well%20%E2%80%94%20but%20she%20saw%20a%20silver%20lining%3A%20Maybe%20it%20was%20finally%20time%20for%20a%20career%20break.%20She%20took%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20year%20off%2C%20soaking%20in%20the%20extra%20time%20with%20her%20husband%20and%20teenage%20daughter.%20Then%20she%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffind-job-searching-hunt-tips-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapplying%20for%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEleven%20months%20and%20300%20applications%20later%2C%20she%20still%20doesn't%20have%20a%20single%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20what's%20going%20on%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20tells%20me.%20She%20has%20a%20great%20resume%20lined%20with%20reputable%20employers%20and%20a%20steady%20ascension%20to%20bigger%20titles.%20And%20as%20a%20recruiting%20executive%2C%20she%20thought%20she%20knew%20how%20to%20navigate%20the%20modern%20job%20market.%20Was%20it%20her%20age%3F%20Her%20experience%3F%20Some%20black%20hole%20sucking%20up%20all%20her%20applications%20before%20they%20ever%20reached%20a%20human%20being%3F%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20about%20what%20I've%20done%20in%20my%20professional%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I'm%20like%2C%20am%20I%20%3Cem%3Ethat%20%3C%2Fem%3Eunemployable%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20question%20I've%20heard%20from%20dozens%20of%20professional%20jobseekers%20I've%20spoken%20to%20over%20the%20last%20two%20years.%20They're%20accomplished%20and%20articulate%20and%20seem%20like%20exactly%20the%20kind%20of%20candidates%20companies%20say%20they%20want.%20Why%20are%20so%20many%20of%20them%20struggling%20in%20an%20economy%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flow-hire-low-fire-layoffs-employees-stuck-unemployment-job-seekers-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elow%20unemployment%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20explanation%20is%20the%20unusual%20nature%20of%20the%20current%20market.%20Many%20businesses%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-collar-recession-hiring-slump-jobs-tech-industry-applications-rejection-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estopped%20hiring%20after%20overstaffing%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20pandemic%2C%20leaving%20too%20few%20openings%20to%20go%20around%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20in%20white-collar%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffind-job-searching-hunt-tips-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emiddle-manager%3C%2Fa%3E%20roles.%20But%20a%20hiring%20slowdown%20alone%20isn't%20enough%20to%20capture%20just%20how%20hellish%20the%20white-collar%20job%20search%20has%20become.%20Something%20deeper%20is%20going%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20heart%20of%20it%20is%20Robinson's%20application%20count%3A%20300.%20A%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20a%20number%20like%20that%20would%20have%20floored%20me.%20Now%2C%20it's%20utterly%20ordinary.%20Two%20other%20people%20I%20spoke%20to%20recently%20told%20me%20they've%20applied%20to%20more%20than%20a%20thousand%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20see%20how%20bad%20it's%20gotten%2C%20I%20asked%20Greenhouse%2C%20one%20of%20the%20leading%20providers%20of%20hiring%20software%2C%20to%20take%20a%20look%20at%20their%20data.%20Last%20quarter%2C%20the%20average%20job%20opening%20received%20242%20applications%20%E2%80%94%20nearly%20triple%20the%20amount%20in%202017%2C%20when%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20was%20at%20a%20comparable%20level.%20That%20means%20that%20when%20someone%20submits%20a%20resume%20today%2C%20they%20have%20the%20abysmally%20low%200.4%25%20chance%20of%20actually%20getting%20the%20job.%20(That's%20just%20for%20the%20%3Cem%3Eaverage%3C%2Fem%3E%20job.%20At%20the%20big-name%20employers%2C%20the%20odds%20are%20even%20worse.)%20Applying%20to%20a%20job%20in%202025%20really%20is%20the%20statistical%20equivalent%20of%20hurling%20your%20resume%20into%20a%20black%20hole.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FP6GEe%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Line%20chart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FP6GEe%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EYou'd%20think%20employers%20would%20be%20loving%20this%2C%20getting%20to%20pick%20from%20such%20a%20big%20pool%20of%20candidates.%20But%20they're%20just%20as%20frustrated.%20Recruiters%20are%20swamped%20with%20resumes%2C%20many%20from%20people%20who%20aren't%20remotely%20qualified%20for%20the%20roles%20they're%20hiring%2C%20and%20they're%20completely%20unequipped%20to%20sort%20through%20the%20deluge.%20The%20result%20is%20something%20far%20more%20dangerous%20than%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-slump-professional-white-collar-jobs-recession-high-salary-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehiring%20slump%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Gridlocked%20to%20the%20point%20of%20paralysis%2C%20the%20job%20market%20isn't%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNobody's%20happy%20with%20the%20current%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Greenhouse%20CEO%20Daniel%20Chait.%20%26quot%3BSomething%20broke%20in%20the%20technology.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20first%20time%20a%20market's%20grown%20so%20overcrowded%20it%20stopped%20functioning.%20Economists%20even%20have%20a%20name%20for%20it%3A%20congestion.%20Big%20markets%20hold%20the%20promise%20of%20creating%20better%20matches%2C%20but%20they%20also%20tend%20to%20devolve%20into%20total%20chaos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCongestion%20is%20the%20bane%20of%20a%20lot%20of%20markets%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Alvin%20Roth%2C%20a%20Nobel%20Prize-winning%20economist%20at%20Stanford%20who's%20helped%20design%20programs%20to%20better%20match%20students%20with%20schools%2C%20organ%20donors%20with%20patients%2C%20and%20hospitals%20with%20new%20doctors.%20%26quot%3BSuccessful%20marketplaces%20have%20to%20fight%20hard%20to%20defeat%20congestion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20what%20happened%20in%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20romantic%20equivalent%20of%20job%20sites%2C%20online%20dating.%20Gaining%20access%20to%20a%20seemingly%20infinite%20number%20of%20potential%20partners%2C%20men%20bombarded%20the%20inboxes%20of%20the%20hottest%20women.%20Overwhelmed%2C%20those%20women%20didn't%20reply.%20So%20the%20men%20messaged%20even%20more%20women%2C%20sending%20generic%20%26quot%3Bhey%26quot%3Bs%20they%20could%20recycle%20over%20and%20over%20again.%20The%20women%20hated%20that%20even%20more.%20The%20result%3F%20A%20vicious%20cycle%20of%20spam%20and%20rejection.%20Few%20people%20found%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20three%20decades%2C%20something%20similar%20has%20played%20out%20in%20the%20labor%20market.%20Before%20the%20internet%2C%20job%20seekers%20had%20to%20pore%20over%20the%20classifieds%20in%20newspapers%2C%20trek%20to%20Kinko's%20to%20print%20out%20their%20resumes%2C%20and%20mail%20them%20off%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20wait%20weeks%20or%20months%20to%20hear%20back.%20Job%20sites%20like%20Monster%20and%20CareerBuilder%20changed%20all%20that%2C%20centralizing%20job%20listings%20into%20one%20searchable%20forum%20and%20letting%20people%20apply%20on%20the%20spot.%20Every%20innovation%20since%20then%20%E2%80%94%20from%20email%20job%20alerts%20to%20LinkedIn's%20Easy%20Apply%20button%20%E2%80%94%20made%20applying%20ever%20more%20seamless.%20That%20very%20convenience%2C%20though%2C%20also%20encouraged%20people%20to%20send%20out%20more%20applications.%20Recruiters%20tried%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20influx%2C%20learning%20to%20skim%20resumes%20in%20mere%20seconds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tipping%20point%2C%20Chait%20says%2C%20came%20when%20ChatGPT%20arrived%20just%20as%20companies%20slammed%20the%20brakes%20on%20hiring.%20Faced%20with%20fewer%20callbacks%2C%20candidates%20turned%20to%20AI%20to%20churn%20out%20more%20applications%2C%20customizing%20resumes%20and%20cover%20letters%20to%20each%20job%20at%20the%20click%20of%20a%20button.%20Some%20even%20deployed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-applications-hiring-ai-bots-spam-resume-cover-letter-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebots%20to%20mass-apply%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20their%20behalf.%20In%20a%20recent%20Greenhouse%20survey%2C%2074%25%20of%20candidates%20said%20they%20use%20AI%20in%20their%20job%20search.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-job-market-ageism-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurge%20in%20volume%20increased%20competition%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20each%20job%20even%20further%2C%20prompting%20people%20to%20cast%20wider%20nets%20and%20apply%20to%20roles%20they%20were%20less%20suited%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecruiters%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20were%20left%20to%20manage%20the%20flood%20alone.%20And%20as%20companies%20shrank%20their%20HR%20teams%20in%20the%20white-collar%20downturn%2C%20the%20workload%20only%20grew.%20On%20Greenhouse%2C%20the%20applications-to-recruiter%20ratio%20is%20now%20500%20to%201%2C%20four%20times%20what%20it%20was%20four%20years%20ago.%20Stretched%20thin%2C%20recruiters%20resorted%20to%20emergency%20triage%20%E2%80%94%20say%2C%20skimming%20only%20the%20first%20100%20resumes%2C%20or%20considering%20just%20the%20candidates%20with%20referrals.%20That's%20come%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20missing%20out%20on%20so%20many%20qualified%20candidates.%20Which%20has%20led%20to%20a%20bizarre%20observation%20I'm%20hearing%20from%20more%20and%20more%20companies%3A%20They're%20getting%20no%20shortage%20of%20eager%20applicants%2C%20but%20they're%20still%20having%20a%20hard%20time%20finding%20good%20hires.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20forces%20that%20make%20it%20cheap%20to%20send%20more%20applications%20are%20working%20faster%20than%20the%20forces%20that%20allow%20you%20to%20quickly%20process%20many%20applications%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Roth.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20deep%20into%20congestion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EChait%20started%20seeing%20the%20warning%20signs%20in%20late%202022.%20But%20it%20was%20last%20year%20that%20he%20remembers%20thinking%3A%20%26quot%3BOK%2C%20this%20is%20%3Cem%3Ereally%3C%2Fem%3E%20happening.%26quot%3B%20Suddenly%20the%20crisis%20was%20everywhere%3A%20in%20Greenhouse's%20data%2C%20in%20its%20surveys%20of%20jobseekers%2C%20in%20conversations%20with%20customers.%20So%20he%20marshalled%20his%20staff%20to%20try%20every%20fix%20they%20could%20imagine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20first%20was%20a%20new%20website%20where%20candidates%20can%20manage%20their%20applications%20to%20Greenhouse's%20clients.%20There%2C%20it%20introduced%20a%20feature%20called%20Dream%20Job%2C%20which%20lets%20people%20mark%20one%20application%20a%20month%20as%20a%20job%20they%20especially%20want.%20The%20idea%20is%20that%20recruiters%20don't%20just%20want%20qualified%20applicants.%20They%20want%20to%20know%20%E2%80%94%20amid%20the%20sea%20of%20people%20applying%20with%20a%20single%20click%20%E2%80%94%20who's%20actually%20serious%20enough%20that%20they'd%20likely%20accept%20an%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnline%20daters%20might%20recognize%20the%20concept%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Brose%26quot%3B%20on%20Hinge%20or%20the%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20like%26quot%3B%20on%20Tinder%20%E2%80%94%20gestures%20borrowed%20from%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.stanford.edu%2F~niederle%2FLee.Niederle.Rose.ExpEcon.2015.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elandmark%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20market%20design.%20Dream%20Job%20launched%20in%20June%2C%20and%20the%20early%20data%20is%20promising%3A%20Employers%20have%20been%20five%20times%20more%20likely%20to%20hire%20Dream%20Job%20applicants%20than%20standard%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20intermediaries%20of%20the%20job%20market%20are%20trying%20their%20own%20fixes.%20LinkedIn%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20introduced%20its%20own%20%26quot%3Brose%2C%26quot%3B%20called%20Top%20Choice%2C%20to%20its%20premium%20members%20(Top%20Choice%20candidates%2C%20the%20platform%20says%2C%20are%2043%25%20more%20likely%20to%20get%20a%20recruiter%20message).%20It%20also%20shows%20people%20whether%20they're%20a%20high%2C%20medium%2C%20or%20low%20match%20for%20the%20roles%20they%20view%20(%26quot%3Btry%20exploring%20other%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20gently%20advises%20low-match%20candidates).%20And%20this%20year%20it's%20been%20testing%20daily%20limits%20on%20Easy%20Apply%20submissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20these%20measures%20might%20help%20on%20the%20margins%2C%20to%20me%20they%20feel%20like%20slapping%20band-aids%20on%20a%20severed%20limb.%20In%20the%20age%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-applicants-use-ai-in-job-search-poll-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI-generated%20mass%20applications%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20companies%20will%20never%20be%20able%20to%20keep%20up%20until%20they%20have%20tools%20that%20can%20evaluate%20candidates%20at%20scale%20%E2%80%94%20and%20so%20far%20those%20tools%20have%20been%20lacking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJob%20seekers%20now%20widely%20assume%20employers%20are%20already%20using%20AI%20to%20reject%20them.%20In%20reality%2C%20many%20of%20the%20companies%20I've%20spoken%20to%20have%20been%20hesitant%20to%20adopt%20AI%20screening%2C%20fearing%20they'll%20run%20afoul%20of%20regulations%20banning%20potentially%20discriminatory%20hiring%20practices.%20Their%20caution%20makes%20sense%3A%20Already%2C%20a%20group%20of%20job%20seekers%20has%20sued%20Workday%2C%20alleging%20its%20AI-powered%20technology%20disproportionately%20screens%20out%20older%20candidates.%20In%20May%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20let%20the%20case%20move%20forward%20as%20a%20collective%20action%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20more%20people%20to%20join%20the%20lawsuit.%20%26quot%3BWe%20deny%20the%20allegations%20in%20the%20suit%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Workday%20spokesperson%20wrote%20in%20an%20email.%20%26quot%3BOur%20products%2C%20both%20AI-enabled%20and%20not%2C%20are%20built%20to%20help%20our%20customers%20manage%20this%20increasing%20volume%20of%20applicants%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20human%20decision-making.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreenhouse%20is%20taking%20a%20different%20approach.%20It's%20testing%20a%20tool%20that%2C%20for%20every%20job%20opening%2C%20allows%20hiring%20managers%20to%20essentially%20teach%20the%20system%20the%20kind%20of%20candidates%20it's%20looking%20for%2C%20ranking%20which%20attributes%20matter%20most.%20The%20company%20plans%20to%20roll%20it%20out%20to%20a%20broader%20set%20of%20customers%20next%20year.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20help%20you%20do%20it%20more%20rapidly%20with%20an%20algorithm%2C%26quot%3B%20Chait%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20not%20like%20there's%20a%20secret%20Greenhouse%20algorithm%20that's%20going%20to%20tell%20you%20who%20to%20look%20at.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that%20works%2C%20it%20could%20be%20an%20improvement%20on%20the%20current%20market%2C%20where%20so%20many%20qualified%20resumes%20go%20unseen.%20Still%2C%20it%20assumes%20hiring%20managers%20know%20what%20they're%20looking%20for%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20what%20they%20want%20is%20in%20fact%20what%20the%20company%20needs.%20Roth%2C%20who's%20spent%20much%20of%20his%20career%20studying%20different%20labor%20markets%2C%20notes%20there's%20still%20so%20much%20we%20don't%20understand%20about%20how%20we%20decide%20who%20to%20hire%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20the%20intuition%20behind%20those%20decisions%20that%20might%20be%20hard%20for%20software%20to%20replicate.%20%26quot%3BHuman%20beings%20are%20still%20good%20at%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20machines%20aren't%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20sort%20of%20wired%20to%20figure%20out%20who%20we%20are%20like%20and%20who%20we%20should%20like%20and%20who's%20on%20our%20team%20and%20could%20be%20on%20our%20team.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobinson%2C%20the%20recruiting%20executive%2C%20prided%20herself%20on%20that%20very%20intuition%20throughout%20her%20career.%20For%20her%2C%20a%20good%20hire%20doesn't%20emerge%20from%20a%20mechanical%20formula%20of%20credentials%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20about%20recognizing%20the%20potential%20of%20who%20the%20candidate%20could%20become.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20be%20so%20close-minded%20to%20say%2C%20'Oh%2C%20you%20have%20to%20check%20all%20the%20boxes%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20table%20now%2C%20it's%20the%20kind%20of%20potential%20she%20longs%20for%20someone%20to%20see%20in%20her.%20But%20every%20rejection%20has%20made%20it%20harder%20and%20harder%20to%20hold%20out%20that%20hope%2C%20and%20in%20this%20broken%20job%20market%2C%20she%20can't%20afford%20to%20wait%20forever.%20For%20now%2C%20she's%20taken%20a%20job%20at%20a%20grocery%20store%20so%20her%20daughter%20won't%20have%20to%20quit%20figure%20skating.%20%26quot%3BIt%20breaks%20my%20heart%20that%20I%20can't%20provide%20what%20I%20was%20providing%2C%26quot%3B%20Robinson%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20want%20to%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faki-ito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAki%20Ito%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftechnology-broke-job-market-at